message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Ukraine, you have a few options depending on your preferences and circumstances:

1. Walking: Walking is a simple and healthy option if you are able and have enough time. Make sure to follow pedestrian paths or sidewalks and be cautious of traffic.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, it can be a convenient and environmentally friendly way to reach the grocery store. Ukraine has designated bike lanes in some cities.

3. Public transportation: Ukraine has an extensive public transportation network, including buses, trams, and trolleybuses. Check the local schedules and routes to see if there is a suitable option to reach your destination.

4. Taxi: Taxis are widely available in Ukraine, and you can use ride-hailing apps like Uber or Bolt to book a taxi conveniently. This option can be costlier than others but offers convenience and saves time.

5. Driving: If you have a car or access to one, driving is an option. Remember to familiarize yourself with local traffic rules and parking options.

Consider the available options and choose the one that suits your needs, taking into account the distance, convenience, cost, and time available.
